organic_results.title: Does employment during high school impair academic progress?
organic_results.snippet: Recently voiced concerns regarding declining standards of academic excellence suggest reason for alarm at burgeoning levels of employment among high school youth. This article documents the extent of high school employment and evaluates its relationship to study time, free time spent at school, class rank, knowledge of occupational tasks, and the probability of dropping out before completing high school. Results show that more extensive work involvement is associated with decreased study time and decreased free time at school …
